trials.page_content: Mupors are very social creatures. Most of them live in extended family groups consisting of multiple generations. Most of them also build large triangular rebos made of clay and grass.

Kazzes are a kind of plant that grow all over Dax. They produce fruit in the springtime, but the fruit is poisonous to animals. No feps eat kazzes nor do they come close. Kazzes can be highly toxic and this poison is a defensive mechanism for kazzes.

The aliens have many different kinds of specialized skills and trades, such as basket weaving. Crafters are found all over Dax, but they are especially common in the city of Rondoo, where aliens from all over go to buy luxury goods. To help make themselves known, crafters join guilds with other crafters of the same trade. Basket weavers are part of the Tinno guild and the Farza guild.
trials.query_predicate: are part of the Tinno guild
trials.predicate_1: are part of the Tinno guild
trials.predicate_2: are part of the Farza guild

trials.page_content: Wopis are extremely rare creatures. They only live in the desert and they all are very hard to find. Wopis sleep during the day to avoid the heat, and look for food at night when it's cool.

Kweps hunt in packs. Even though they are pack animals, all of them have highly idiosyncractic food preferences and behaviors. Some of them like to eat apples and others like to eat oranges. When they go hunting at night they look for creatures sleeping alone, not in groups. Right before they go hunting, the kweps chew on xorfun and on tunkel.

Reesles are strange, furry creatures, often found in the homes of the aliens. They are not house pets but quasi-domesticated animals. They will steal food from you if you are not paying attention. They have special headgear to help other aliens identify their owners. Around their heads, they wear giant wutsats and carry sticks with them.
Glippets are large creatures, quite intelligent, with a life-span of about sixty years. They live on the southern continent of Caro.
trials.query_predicate: live on the continent of Caro
trials.predicate_1: live on the continent of Caro
trials.predicate_2: live on the continent of Este

trials.page_content: Krens are a tribe of the aliens that live on the continent of Benli, which has no agriculture. Like most creatures on Dax, Krens eat other creatures to survive. Animals like stups, four-legged creatures with large antlers, are a resource for the Krens. Stups roam all over the windy highlands of Benli, far from the oceans. Krens are stup-herders and sing songs to the stups to help them relax.
Isooms are tree-like plants that are found in hilly regions of Fale. Their fruit is edible, and the aliens often cultivate isooms for food. Isooms produce fruit with bumpy skin.

Apaffs are a nuisance for the aliens. They make burrows everywhere including in the middle of farmland and in front of their houses. But most aliens find apaffs cute, and tolerate them to some extent. Some aliens even like to keep them as pets.

Vimbles are social insects that live in colonies of up to a thousand individuals. Vimbles live for a year or less. They have a single queen, who must find somewhere to hibernate over the winter before starting a new colony. Vimble queens hibernate in fallen logs.
trials.predicate_2: hibernate in the abandoned burrows of other animals

trials.page_content: Mooks are ferocious creatures that live on the continent of Benli. Benli has dramatic elevation changes unlike any other continent on Dax. Animals find terrority in locations that will maximize their chances of survival. Mooks have territories at the tops of tall mountains.
trials.query_predicate: have territories at the tops of tall mountains
trials.predicate_1: have territories at the tops of tall mountains
trials.predicate_2: have territories at the bottom of deep canyons

trials.page_content: Blins are small creatures. They all have hollow bones and fly. They sing beautiful songs to attract mates and distract their enemies when they attack.

Batozes are large birds that are found along all the coasts of Dax. They are skilled hunters and can fly for whole days without stopping. They use their sharp claws to hunt for fish. They also have special wings that are light but powerful. Batozes have six wings and seven wings.

Nannus only feed on rare flowers called lodeks. Most lodeks only bloom for one day a year, and most have purple petals. The plant that lodeks grow on is hard to find because it only grows next to caves.
trials.query_predicate: only bloom for one day a year
trials.predicate_1: only bloom for one day a year

trials.page_content: The morseth is an animal that lives part of its life in the sea and part of its life on land. Most morseths come on land to find mates and to bury their dead. Most morseths build permanent structures called fendles in order to bury their dead kin, and fendles are usually made out of wood.
trials.predicate_2: come on land to find mates

trials.page_content: The soil on the continent of Aga is very fertile, and the aliens have learned to grow many crops. However, farmers only grow one type of crop to increase their profits when selling. Their farms are very big, often stretching several miles in every direction. During the springtime, the aliens flood their fields to plant fujusi.
trials.query_predicate: flood their fields to plant fujusi
trials.predicate_1: flood their fields to plant fujusi
trials.predicate_2: burn their fields to plant soroneeks

trials.page_content: Yomis are small, fast insect-like creatures. They all live in the borderland woodlands. They all fly towards the mountains in search of food, but they need to be careful of their natural predators, turmens.
trials.predicate_2: fly towards the mountains in search of food

trials.page_content: Ollers spend most of their lives in water, but occasionally come on land to gather berries. Ollers use tools on land but have a difficult time making them. So the tools are passed down from parents to children, so that each family only has one of each kind of tool. Baby ollers find it very exciting to be on land, but they have trouble walking and need to be carried by members of their families. While on land, ollers carry their young in guklags.

Kaples are small animals that live in the jungles. They are most active at dawn and at dusk, when their usual predators are less active. Their thick fur helps camouflage them among the plants on the forest floor. Kaples have striped fur and spotted fur.
